spathose.d:
a. See Spathic.
a. Having a spathe; resembling a spathe; spatheceous;
   spathal.

spectroscopists.d:
plural of spectroscopist
n. One who investigates by means of a spectroscope;
   one skilled in the use of the spectroscope.

spheral.d:
a. Of or pertaining to a sphere or the spheres.
a. Rounded like a sphere; sphere-shaped; hence, symmetrical;
   complete; perfect.

sportful.d:
a. Full of sport; merry; frolicsome; full of jesting;
   indulging in mirth or play; playful; wanton; as, a sportful companion.
a. Done in jest, or for mere play; sportive.
